Cape Town - A horror crash in Bellville, Cape Town, left two people dead in the early hours of Sunday morning. Seven other people sustained various injuries, ER24 spokesperson Werner Vermaak said. "Two people were killed and seven others sustained various injuries in a collision on the N1 near Durban Road in Bellville. "During the early hours of this morning, paramedics arrived on the scene where they found one vehicle overturned and several others with severe damages," Vermaak said. "Sadly, two people were found with fatal injuries. Seven others sustained various injuries and were treated on the scene before being transported to hospital.
 
"The exact circumstances surrounding the collision is not yet known," he said. Cape Argus